related_questions.question: What is the difference sparkling wine and Champagne?
related_questions.snippet: The easy and short answer is that sparkling wine can only be called champagne if it comes from the Champagne region in northern France, just outside of Paris. There are several types of sparkling wine; the most common are champagne, prosecco from Italy, cava from Spain and sparkling wine from Australia.

buttons.subtitle: Sparkling Wine Region Of Origin
buttons.title: Who Invented Sparkling Wine? How England Paved the Way
buttons.snippet: It was actually the British who first took a vested interest in what made the sparkle of sparkling wine. Still wine would be imported from Champagne in France in barrels. Cold winters in this region meant that the wine would temporarily stop fermenting, meaning sugar and dormant yeast were left.
